        <body>
            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_001340_0001" n="0001"/><!-- Change both @facs and @n -->
	<!-- Start each page with a <pb> formatted as above -->

<!-- If this is a letter or similar with an opener (with content such as dateline and/or salute) add it. For example: -->
<lb/><opener><add hand="#U" rend="gray small">Acc 6630<space extent="2" unit="words"/>39 <space extent="3" unit="words"/>33</add>
<lb/><dateline><space extent="5" unit="words"/><placeName><settlement type="village">Senna</settlement></placeName> <date when="1858-07-13">13<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> July
<lb/><space extent="7" unit="words"/>1858</date></dateline><!-- Change line info as appropriate -->
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><salute>Sir</salute></opener><!-- Change line info as appropriate -->
<lb/><p>The <term type="people">Portugese</term> are
<lb/>all of opinion that
<lb/>the village of <placeName><geogName type="village">Nyaruka</geogName></placeName>
<lb/>is nearer to this 
<lb/>than any point
<lb/>that can be approached
<lb/>here. <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>I think it will</p>
<lb/><ab> <add place="marginleft" rend="gray diagonal" hand="#U">£5500</add> <persName>Commander Bedingfeld <choice><abbr>R.N.</abbr><expan>Royal Navy</expan></choice></persName></ab>

	<pb facs="liv_001340_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">be the best plan to get
<lb/>up the steam in the morning
<lb/>and go down to it.  I shall
<lb/>meet you there about
<lb/>10 o clock -</p>
<lb/><p>The <term type="people">Portuguese</term> here have
<lb/>no canoes or Launches
<lb/>as all were sent down
<lb/>to meet the <persName>Governor</persName>
<lb/>and were behind the
<lb/><placeName><geogName type="island">island near <placeName><settlement type="village">Mazaro</settlement></placeName></geogName></placeName>
<lb/>where we met the officer

	<pb facs="liv_001340_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>He is expected there daily &amp; <add place="marginright" hand="#U" rend="gray">34</add>
<lb/>we may arrange with
<lb/>him about them - <persName><choice><abbr>L<hi rend="sup">t</hi></abbr><expan>Lieutenant</expan></choice>
<lb/><unclear>Ferraõ</unclear></persName> has put two
<lb/>rooms at our service
<lb/>I go to see them tonight
<lb/>Please wind up my
<lb/>watch in the locker
<lb/>They tell me that the
<lb/>other side of the river<!-- geog: -->
<lb/>is always the deepest &amp;
<lb/>best even up to <placeName><settlement type="village">Tete</settlement></placeName></p>
<!-- If there is a letter or similar with a closer with content such as salute or signed -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="1" unit="words"/>I am &amp;c <persName><choice><abbr>D.</abbr><expan>David</expan></choice> Livingstone</persName><!-- Change as appropriate --></p>

	<pb facs="liv_001340_0004" n="0004"/>
	<cb rend="vertical"/>
<ab><address>
<addrLine><persName>Commander Bedingfeld <choice><abbr>R.N.</abbr><expan>Royal Navy</expan></choice></persName></addrLine>
<addrLine><space extent="2" unit="words"/>Ma Robert<!-- This is DL's boat --></addrLine>
</address></ab>
	
